The Single Most Important Question to Answer

Are ORA-12805 errors appearing in the alert log
IMMEDIATELY BEFORE each domain reconfig entry?

Or are domain reconfigs happening INDEPENDENTLY
of ORA-12805?


If ORA-12805 always precedes each reconfig — the PX slave death is driving the domain churn and the fix is in the PX layer.
If domain reconfigs are happening without ORA-12805 preceding them — the GRD/interconnect layer is the primary problem and PX slave deaths are a downstream consequence.
That single correlation is the pivot point of the entire RCA. Everything else I have stated — including my self-correction — remains hypothesis until that question is answered.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​





